**who —** NINTENDO WII U — an exereunesis sphere — the teardown

**what —** The Wii U paired a modest tri-core PowerPC and an AMD GPU with its real idea: a tablet-like GamePad with a built-in touchscreen for off-TV and second-screen play. Confusing marketing and weak sales made it a commercial failure — yet its core concept was vindicated, scaled up, by the Switch.

**where —** the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored  Framework inputs: the chips; the buses; the spec; the lore  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** The Wii U paired a modest tri-core PowerPC and an AMD GPU with its real idea: a tablet-like GamePad with a built-in touchscreen for off-TV and second-screen play. Confusing marketing and weak sales made it a commercial failure — yet its core concept was vindicated, scaled up, by the Switch.

